cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation and Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM) using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves computer graphics and rendering techniques, which suggests the category cs.GR (Graphics). The use of SLAM indicates the category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses domain adaptation techniques, which are commonly used in the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
